  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2009_Solutions_2009s_page_002_18",
    "text": "have no common zero in (0,1)?. Namely, for the first partial to vanish, we must have xo = 1/2 since 1 + yo is nowhere zero, but for xo = 1/2 the second partial cannot vanish.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
